<br>
I've been screwed out of a few things, but it didn't ruin my life. I just found other ways to get what I needed, or changed my priorities.<br>
<br>
One such incident was trying to raise my faction with Cabilis and Firiona Vie by slaughtering goblins and sabertooths. Of course, I got there too late, and the fangs I needed were trivial, as were the goblin headbands. I got pissed off, I ranted - and then I researched other ways to gain the faction I desired. (Faction raising is one of the most important quests for my ranger.)<br>
<br>
There were other things I wanted but outlevelled -- Whimsy Larktwitter's magical bow, the Bootstrutter's 10-slot weight reduction pack quest, pieces for my Trueshot -- but I found ways around them. Helpful guildmates and friends, and finding similar equipment that wasn't affected by TLC. It isn't the end of the world.<br>
